@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit Zero Downtime Rollout

' Argo CD applies the new image. Kubernetes brings up the new pod, waits for it to
' be healthy, then kills the old one. The old pod serves the whole time.

actor Users
participant "Argo CD" as argo
participant "Deployment\n(maxSurge 1, maxUnavailable 0)" as deploy
participant "old pod v1" as v1
participant "new pod v2" as v2

Users -> v1 : serving traffic

argo -> deploy : apply new image tag
deploy -> v2 : start new pod
note right of v2 : v1 still serves while v2 starts

deploy -> v2 : wait for the readiness probe to pass
v2 --> deploy : ready

deploy -> Users : send new traffic to v2
deploy -> v1 : terminate old pod
Users -> v2 : serving traffic

note over v1, v2
  the old pod is killed only after the new one is healthy,
  so there is no downtime
end note

@enduml
